<TEXT>
government troops broke through rebel 
cordons at a besieged army garrison securing an important victory 
in sri lankas civil war military officials said monday 
at least 53 tamil rebels were killed over the weekend in bitter 
handtohand fighting said the officials who spoke on condition 
of anonymity they did not mention any army casualties 
the garrison in the northern district of mullaitivu 175 miles 
northeast of colombo is in heavy jungle tamil rebels are believed 
to have set up their headquarters in the area 
the military officials said troop reinforcements parachuted into 
the garrison and others fought their way to the camp from the 
