pope john paul ii on monday lamented 
that millions of people are living in misery because of the failure 
of development policies but he urged africans not to give up hope 
despite so much poverty and suffering so many instances of 
neglect and injustice the final word is not one of suffering 
and hopelessness but of love and victory over sin he said 
the pope on the third day of a 10day fournation african 
