ethnic albanians staged a general 
strike monday to protest serbian rule in kosovo province in 
defiance of warnings that they would face suspension or lose their 
jobs 
we are striking to show how we feel about the bad situation in 
kosovo for albanians said salem lepaja a university lecturer 
the strike was called by independent trade unions set up 
recently by kosovos 19 million ethnic albanians who make up 90 
percent of its population 
serbias communist government took administrative control of 
kosovo last spring saying it had to abolish the provinces 
autonomy to protect the serb minority from alleged harassment by 
the majority ethnic albanians 
in july the kosovo parliament proclaimed the provinces 
independence from serbia which reacted by dismissing the lawmakers 
streets in this provincial capital were virtually deserted 
monday almost all shops were closed pristinas usually lively 
bazaar was deserted with empty stalls the previous days trash 
strewn about and a big metal gate chained shut 
there were no reports of violence last week serbian 
authorities said 21 police and scores of demonstrators were injured 
in clashes with thousands of ethnic albanians waiting for a us 
congressional delegation investigating charges of human rights 
abuses 
