the problem is that irresponsibility like this press release 
can kill a bank ellen stockdale a spokeswoman for the 
comptroller of the currency in washington which regulates 
federally chartered banks said after dimauros statement appeared 
dimauro later apologized blaming an aide for releasing a 
statement without his final approval and the banks stock more 
than doubled the next day rising 112 to 212 
the incident highlights just how jittery investors and others 
watching the market have become in particular it demonstrates an 
uncertainty about banks sparked by the savings and loan crisis and 
the recent spate of bank failures nationwide banks traditionally 
are considered conservative reliable financial institutions 
for the first time since 1933 people are wondering whether 
or not they have their savings or deposits in the right bank the 
one that will not fail howell said that is the most 
significant change in thinking in the postworld war ii period 
howell and ayers agreed that the recent problems in the banking 
industry have been sparked in part because there are too many 
banks and the industry is adjusting 
there are between 13000 and 14000 commercial banks in the 
country and about 4500 savings banks they said 
we dont need any of the 4500 period you can just mark them 
off howell said 
rumors may threaten to become selffulfilling prophecies until 
the economy levels off ayers said 
i think a lot will depend on the health of the economy he 
said i think if we can sidestep recession nationally these 
rumors this falloff in confidence will gradually arrest itself 
</TEXT>
